# **03  Key decisions — with rationale**

## **Product decisions**

| **ID** | **Decision** | **Rationale** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **D-001** | 6 features deferred to Phase TBD: F-24 (Order Instead CTA), F-27 (Grocery list), F-28 (Ingredient check-off), F-46 (Freemium tier visible), F-50 (Referral), F-57 (Daily email digest) | Simplify MVP scope. Grocery features consolidated. No monetisation signalling before habit forms. Referral requires freemium first. Founder to assign exact phases next planning session. |
| **D-002** | F-59 My Meals tab added to MVP — replaces Grocery tab in 5-tab nav bar | Cooking history is genuinely useful in MVP and needs no external integration. Grocery tab depended on F-27/F-28 which are deferred. |
| **D-003** | Onboarding updated from prototype analysis: OB-00 (conversational intro, no skip) added. OB-03 includes migration duration slider. OB-07 is left/right card swipe with visible ♥/✕ buttons. OB-08b (plan preview) added. | Prototype showed more engaging onboarding. Migration duration feeds RE city overlay weight. Left/right swipe more intuitive. Plan preview creates aha moment before user enters the app. |
| **D-004** | OB-07 dish preference pool: Indian-only. Idli Sambar, Poha, Aloo Paratha, Rajma Chawal, Masala Dosa, Paneer Butter Masala, Chole Bhature, Dal Makhani, Khichdi, Biryani. No Pizza. No Pasta. | Foofoo is Indian-first. Western dishes produce RE signals the cohort matrix cannot use. Showing Pizza sets wrong product expectation. |
| **D-005** | Long-press gesture removed from entire product. Replaced: swipe left on card → reveal Not Today (amber) + Never (red) buttons. Carousel now via tap on swap icon, not left swipe. | Long-press is a hidden gesture with no affordance. Swipe-reveal is platform-native (iOS Mail, Gmail, WhatsApp). Every action now has a visible entry point. |
| **D-006** | DOC-06 is structural specification only. When Figma designs arrive, they override: color palette, typography, component aesthetics, imagery. They do NOT override: wireframes, gesture spec, spacing system. | Founder working on Figma separately. DOC-06 provides engineering defaults and structural authority in the interim. |
| **D-007** | Document format going forward: .docx primary + .md companion for GitHub. Both produced simultaneously for all new documents. | docx for sharing and review. .md for GitHub as source of truth. |

## **Architecture decisions (locked in DOC-10)**

| **ADR** | **Decision** | **Rationale** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **ADR-001** | React Native + Expo SDK 52+ as mobile framework. TypeScript strict mode. | Single codebase iOS + Android. Best AI coding agent support. Expo eliminates native build complexity. Strict mode for allergen data safety. |
| **ADR-002** | Supabase as entire backend. ap-south-1 (Mumbai) region. | PostgreSQL mandatory for RE queries. Free tier adequate to 500 DAU. Open-source exit path. Mumbai = lowest latency for Indian users. |
| **ADR-003** | RE implemented as Supabase Edge Functions at MVP (not separate microservice). RE has its own schema (re_engine) and versioned API endpoints. | Zero additional infrastructure. Adjacent to DB (low latency for RE queries). Migration to dedicated service planned for Phase 3 if scale demands it. |
| **ADR-004** | TanStack Query v5 for all server state. | Purpose-built for async server data. MMKV persister for offline plan cache. Background refresh, deduplication, stale-while-revalidate built in. |
| **ADR-005** | MMKV for all local persistence (not AsyncStorage). | 10× faster. Synchronous reads for offline plan display (no flicker). Supports encryption for DPDP compliance. |
| **ADR-006** | Expo Router v3 for navigation. | File = route. Maps directly to DOC-05 screen IDs. Deep linking automatic. |
| **ADR-007** | FlashList (Shopify) over FlatList for all scrollable lists. | 5× less blank flash on fast scroll. Significantly better on Pixel 3a reference device. |
| **ADR-008** | OneSignal for push notifications. | Single SDK for iOS + Android. Scheduling built in for 7 AM IST delivery. Free tier adequate for MVP. |
| **ADR-009** | TypeScript strict mode throughout. No @ts-ignore. No any except documented. | Allergen data is safety-critical. A type error could surface a dish containing an excluded allergen. |

## **RE architecture decisions (non-negotiable)**

| **Decision** | **What it means** | **What violates it** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Class-first architecture — non-negotiable** | Pipeline: cohort → meal class plan → dish expansion. Never dish-first. Never cuisine-first. | Any code that suggests a dish without first assigning a meal class code from the cohort matrix. |
| **RE isolation** | No RE logic in the React Native app. App talks to RE only via /v1/ API contract. | Embedding scoring weights, class codes, or cohort logic anywhere in the app codebase. |
| **Cohort matrix in DB, not hardcoded** | re_engine.cohort_matrix table. Auto-recalibrates weekly. New class = human decision. | Hardcoding class weights or cohort assignments in TypeScript/SQL that bypasses the matrix. |
| **Three SQL safety gate queries are release blockers** | Diet violations, allergen violations, Jain violations — all must return 0 rows before any deploy. | Advancing a sprint or merging to any branch if any query returns > 0 rows. |
| **Annotation columns renamed, never dropped** | Deprecated columns get _FounderInfoOnly suffix. They stay in the schema. | Dropping a column in any migration. |

