# **07  Claude Code operating rules — read before every build session**

These rules apply to every Claude Code session without exception. Paste this section into every Claude Code prompt.

| **RULE 1 — Production deploys require explicit founder approval** Never commit or push to main or develop without the founder saying 'approved' or equivalent in the conversation. Hard stop. **RULE 2 — Hard stop on missing files** If expected folders or files are not found, stop and report. Do not create them speculatively. **RULE 3 — RE safety gates after every RE change** After any change to RE-related code: run the three SQL safety gate queries. All must return 0 rows. If any returns > 0: block, report, do not advance. **RULE 4 — Service role key isolation** SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY goes in Edge Functions only. Never in React Native code. Never committed to git. **RULE 5 — TypeScript strict mode** Zero TypeScript errors before any commit. No @ts-ignore comments. **RULE 6 — Annotation columns renamed, never dropped** When deprecating a DB column, rename it with _FounderInfoOnly suffix. Never write a migration that drops a column. **RULE 7 — Prompts must be self-contained** Every Claude Code prompt must include all context needed for that session — file paths, schema state, relevant doc sections. Sessions lose context between runs. |
